sentences: The Rudolf Barshai International Strings Competition was established in 2020.
Barshai was born on September 28, 1924, in Stanitsa Labinskaya, Krasnodar Krai, in modern-day Russia.
During his career Barshai won numerous Soviet and international competitions and was the founding violist of the Borodin Quartet in 1945, where he remained a member until 1953.

He was the artistic director of the Israel Chamber Orchestra from 1978 to 1981.

Barshai resided in Switzerland until his death in 2010.
